 unter den Leitbegriffen „Pluralität", „Subjektivität" und „Kritik", die als Schlüsselkonzepte der Moderne gelten können.  aThe volume presents the records of the 2017 Schleiermacher Society on the theme “Reformation and Modernity.” They present Schleiermacher not only as a thinker on the translation of the Reformation legacy into modernity, but also as a thinker on interrelationships between other areas of sociocultural life, including social behavior, politics, art, and philosophy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCivilization, ModernvCongresses. 0aReformationvCongresses. 4aKritk. 4aPluralität. 4aReformation. 4aSubjektivität. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aReformation.  acriticism.  aplurality.  asubjectivity.1 aArndt, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarniske, Friedemann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrino, Omar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBukowski, Piotr de Bończa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDhouib, Sarhan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDierken, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDierken, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFabio, Udo Di, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFritz, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerber, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiacca, Emanuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGräbe, Viktoria, econtributor.4ctb4ht